@spec tm_proj_symmetry_spec  src=tests/specs/tm_proj_symmetry_spec.lua  loc=95  sha=652cbb1  cases=2
@exercises harness (harness), trackerManager (h.tm)
@surface   harness.mk, tm:getChannel
@harness   mk{seed.length, seed.resolution, seed.notes}

# Intent
  Projection symmetry: the column-projection step must expose BOTH the
  onset and the tail in the logical frame, never raw.
  
  Before: the logical projection set only evt.ppq = round(ppqL); evt.endppq was
  left as the tail pass's CLIPPED RAW value. So a tv consumer reading
  evt.endppq got a swung, clipped realisation while evt.ppq was logical
  -- the asymmetry this suite pins shut.
  
  After: evt.endppq = endppqL (authored logical ceiling, UNCLIPPED;
  util.OPEN stays OPEN). evt.endppqC = clipped logical ceiling, the
  float inversion of the realised raw tail (render-only; the tp tail
  build is the sole consumer; ctx:isOnGrid owns the row-membership
  tolerance). Raw never appears on the tv surface.
  
  Real tm, real cm under a non-identity swing (classic-55) so a raw
  leak is detectable: logical 600 and swung-raw(600) differ.

# Helpers
  @fn probe()  @ 27
  @fn seeded(notes)  @ 29-35
  @fn noteAt(tm, pitch)  @ 37-41

# Cases
  @case 'finite clipped note: endppq is authored logical, endppqC is clipped logical, neither is raw'  [pure]  @ 45-71
  @case 'open tail: endppq stays util.OPEN, endppqC is the clipped logical render position'  [pure]  @ 75-93

# Uses (outbound edges)
  @use call harness.mk  @ 27
  @use call tm:getChannel  @ 38

